  "text": "Photo by Rocky Luten The holiday season is in full swing, and with shipping deadlines looming, the pressure to find the perfect gift is officially on. It’s also around this time when creative ideas start to dry up and you need some quick inspiration. Maybe you’ve still got a few people on your list who are impossible to shop for. Or maybe you’ve decided to treat yourself this year (anything to hit that free shipping minimum, right?). Luckily our shop is packed with hundreds of thoughtful ideas—and our curated gift guides make finding the perfect pick a whole lot easier. And even better, our team shared what they’re adding to their own wishlists. From a genius citrus juicer to the ultimate frying pan, these are the gifts we’re giving (and crossing our fingers to get) this year. 1. Fredericks \u0026 Mae Multi Confetti Board “The Fredericks and Mae Multi Confetti Board. The colors are so perfect it would make me happy to meal prep.” —Kelly Kenneally, Graphic Designer 2. Dreamfarm Fluicer Citrus Juicers, Set of 2 “I truly cannot believe I've lived this long without owning a Fluicer. I love an at-home margarita, and with this, it won't take me zillions of years to make fresh lime juice. Plus, it folds flat and won't get stuck in my kitchen drawers. Please, Santa!” —Julie Vadnal, Editorial Director 3. Verve Culture Mexican Hot Chocolate “I’m a big cocoa fan, but I’ve never tried proper Mexican hot chocolate. This gift set comes with the tools to make it—and they’re so beautiful, I’d totally keep them out.” —Maurine Hainsworth, Senior Copywriter 4. Formula 67 Wood Conditioner Paste “I’m putting Formula 67 Wood Conditioner Paste in everyone's stocking because it is THE BEST.” —Kat Stewart, CX 5. Holcomb Perch Mortar \u0026 Pestle “I love that you can angle it within the nesting wood so you can get better leverage on whatever you're grinding or mixing. There is also a great rest for the pestle that looks very swanky.” —Kiernan Black, Senior Manager, Creative Ops 5. de Buyer carbon steel fry pan “Another de Buyer carbon steel fry pan. I got one a few months ago and it hasn't left my stove since. It's an absolute work horse. Gets crazy hot. Works in the oven. If it was up to me, I'd have ten of these hanging above my stove. But right now, I'll settle for two.” —Paul Hagopian, Editor We want to know: What's at the top of your wishlist from our Shop? Let us know in the comments! Popular on Food52",
